narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Learned important methodologies, important theories, refined critical thinking skills

I learned a lot of different approaches to thinking about the world and scales of power. I can't really pinpoint what exactly feminist postcolonial thinking might entail. I had never taken a theory course before, so I guess I learned that the world of theory is very confusing.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: A lot of writing! Wish it could have been responses due every other week or perhaps 6 responses overall so as to allow for more engagement with reading. Often felt pressure to write and post something even when wasn't fully through all the readings.

Strengths: interesting material. Weaknesses: the ways in which said material was discussed, posting requirement (via Facebook), overall level of engagement, syllabus/intentions could have been more clear.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes of course! The professor is excellent.
Maybe? I feel like I learned a lot, but not as much as I could have.
Definitely! Undergraduates should take this course too - it is challenging but incredibly rewarding and Prof. Grewal is a fantastic seminar leader
